Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJobSet.name: contentRedaction
Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJobSet.abstract: Settings for content redaction within a transcription job.

Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJobSet.name: languageIdSettings
Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJobSet.abstract: The language identification settings associated with your call analytics job. These settings include VocabularyName, VocabularyFilterName, and LanguageModelName.

Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJobSet.name: languageModelName
Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJobSet.abstract: The structure used to describe a custom language model.

Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJobSet.name: languageOptions
Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJobSet.abstract:
When you run a call analytics job, you can specify the language spoken in the audio, or you can have Amazon Transcribe identify the language for you.

To specify a language, specify an array with one language code. If you don’t know the language, you can leave this field blank and Amazon Transcribe will use machine learning to identify the language for you. To improve the ability of Amazon Transcribe to correctly identify the language, you can provide an array of the languages that can be present in the audio. Refer to Supported languages for additional information.

Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJobSet.name: vocabularyFilterMethod
Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJobSet.abstract: Set to mask to remove filtered text from the transcript and replace it with three asterisks (“***”) as placeholder text. Set to remove to remove filtered text from the transcript without using placeholder text. Set to tag to mark the word in the transcription output that matches the vocabulary filter. When you set the filter method to tag, the words matching your vocabulary filter are not masked or removed.

Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJobSet.name: vocabularyFilterName
Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJobSet.abstract: The name of the vocabulary filter to use when running a call analytics job. The filter that you specify must have the same language code as the analytics job.

Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJobSet.name: vocabularyName
Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJobSet.abstract: The name of a vocabulary to use when processing the call analytics job.

Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJob.ht.name: callAnalyticsJobName
Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJob.ht.abstract: The name of the call analytics job.

Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJob.ht.name: channelDefinitions
Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJob.ht.abstract: Shows numeric values to indicate the channel assigned to the agent’s audio and the channel assigned to the customer’s audio.

Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJob.ht.name: completionTime
Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJob.ht.abstract: A timestamp that shows when the analytics job was completed.

Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJob.ht.name: creationTime
Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJob.ht.abstract: A timestamp that shows when the analytics job was created.

Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJob.ht.name: dataAccessRoleArn
Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJob.ht.abstract: The Amazon Resource Number (ARN) that you use to access the analytics job. ARNs have the format arn:partition:service:region:account-id:resource-type/resource-id.

Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJob.ht.name: failureReason
Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJob.ht.abstract:
If the AnalyticsJobStatus is FAILED, this field contains information about why the job failed.

The FailureReason field can contain one of the following values:

  • Unsupported media format: The media format specified in the MediaFormat field of the request isn’t valid. See the description of the MediaFormat field for a list of valid values.

  • The media format provided does not match the detected media format: The media format of the audio file doesn’t match the format specified in the MediaFormat field in the request. Check the media format of your media file and make sure the two values match.

  • Invalid sample rate for audio file: The sample rate specified in the MediaSampleRateHertz of the request isn’t valid. The sample rate must be between 8,000 and 48,000 Hertz.

  • The sample rate provided does not match the detected sample rate: The sample rate in the audio file doesn’t match the sample rate specified in the MediaSampleRateHertz field in the request. Check the sample rate of your media file and make sure that the two values match.

  • Invalid file size: file size too large: The size of your audio file is larger than what Amazon Transcribe Medical can process. For more information, see Guidelines and Quotas in the Amazon Transcribe Medical Guide.

  • Invalid number of channels: number of channels too large: Your audio contains more channels than Amazon Transcribe Medical is configured to process. To request additional channels, see Amazon Transcribe Medical Endpoints and Quotas in the Amazon Web Services General Reference.

Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJob.ht.name: identifiedLanguageScore
Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJob.ht.abstract: A value between zero and one that Amazon Transcribe assigned to the language that it identified in the source audio. This value appears only when you don’t provide a single language code. Larger values indicate that Amazon Transcribe has higher confidence in the language that it identified.

Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJob.ht.name: languageCode
Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJob.ht.abstract:
If you know the language spoken between the customer and the agent, specify a language code for this field.

If you don’t know the language, you can leave this field blank, and Amazon Transcribe will use machine learning to automatically identify the language. To improve the accuracy of language identification, you can provide an array containing the possible language codes for the language spoken in your audio. Refer to Supported languages for additional information.

Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJob.ht.name: media
Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJob.ht.abstract: Describes the input media file in a transcription request.

Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJob.ht.name: mediaFormat
Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJob.ht.abstract: The format of the input audio file. Note: for call analytics jobs, only the following media formats are supported: MP3, MP4, WAV, FLAC, OGG, and WebM.

Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJob.ht.name: mediaSampleRateHertz
Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJob.ht.abstract: The sample rate, in Hertz, of the audio.

Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJob.ht.name: settings
Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJob.ht.abstract: Provides information about the settings used to run a transcription job.

Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJob.ht.name: startTime
Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJob.ht.abstract: A timestamp that shows when the analytics job started processing.

Classes/AWSTranscribeAbsoluteTimeRange.h.name: endTime
Classes/AWSTranscribeAbsoluteTimeRange.h.abstract:
A value that indicates the end of the time range in milliseconds. To set absolute time range, you must specify a start time and an end time. For example, if you specify the following values:

  • StartTime - 10000

  • Endtime - 50000

The time range is set between 10,000 milliseconds and 50,000 milliseconds into the call.

Classes/AWSTranscribeAbsoluteTimeRange.h.name: first
Classes/AWSTranscribeAbsoluteTimeRange.h.abstract: A time range from the beginning of the call to the value that you’ve specified. For example, if you specify 100000, the time range is set to the first 100,000 milliseconds of the call.

Classes/AWSTranscribeAbsoluteTimeRange.h.name: last
Classes/AWSTranscribeAbsoluteTimeRange.h.abstract: A time range from the value that you’ve specified to the end of the call. For example, if you specify 100000, the time range is set to the last 100,000 milliseconds of the call.

Classes/AWSTranscribeAbsoluteTimeRange.h.name: startTime
Classes/AWSTranscribeAbsoluteTimeRange.h.abstract:
A value that indicates the beginning of the time range in seconds. To set absolute time range, you must specify a start time and an end time. For example, if you specify the following values:

  • StartTime - 10000

  • Endtime - 50000

The time range is set between 10,000 milliseconds and 50,000 milliseconds into the call.

Classes/AWSTranscribeAbsoluteTimeRange.h.name: AWSTranscribeAbsoluteTimeRange
Classes/AWSTranscribeAbsoluteTimeRange.h.abstract: A time range, set in seconds, between two points in the call.

Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJob.ht.name: AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJob
Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJob.ht.abstract: Describes an asynchronous analytics job that was created with the StartAnalyticsJob operation.

Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJobSum.name: AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJobSummary
Classes/AWSTranscribeCallAnalyticsJobSum.abstract: Provides summary information about a call analytics job.

Classes/AWSTranscribeCategoryProperties..name: AWSTranscribeCategoryProperties
Classes/AWSTranscribeCategoryProperties..abstract: An object that contains the rules and additional information about a call analytics category.

Classes/AWSTranscribeChannelDefinition.h.name: AWSTranscribeChannelDefinition
Classes/AWSTranscribeChannelDefinition.h.abstract: For a call analytics job, an object that indicates the audio channel that belongs to the agent and the audio channel that belongs to the customer.

Classes/AWSTranscribeContentRedaction.ht.name: AWSTranscribeContentRedaction
Classes/AWSTranscribeContentRedaction.ht.abstract: Settings for content redaction within a transcription job.

Classes/AWSTranscribeInputDataConfig.htm.name: AWSTranscribeInputDataConfig
Classes/AWSTranscribeInputDataConfig.htm.abstract: The object that contains the Amazon S3 object location and access role required to train and tune your custom language model.

Classes/AWSTranscribeInterruptionFilter..name: AWSTranscribeInterruptionFilter
Classes/AWSTranscribeInterruptionFilter..abstract: An object that enables you to configure your category to be applied to call analytics jobs where either the customer or agent was interrupted.

Classes/AWSTranscribeJobExecutionSetting.name: AWSTranscribeJobExecutionSettings
Classes/AWSTranscribeJobExecutionSetting.abstract: Provides information about when a transcription job should be executed.

Classes/AWSTranscribeLanguageIdSettings..name: AWSTranscribeLanguageIdSettings
Classes/AWSTranscribeLanguageIdSettings..abstract: Language-specific settings that can be specified when language identification is enabled.

Classes/AWSTranscribeLanguageModel.html.name: AWSTranscribeLanguageModel
Classes/AWSTranscribeLanguageModel.html.abstract: The structure used to describe a custom language model.

Classes/AWSTranscribeMedia.html.name: AWSTranscribeMedia
Classes/AWSTranscribeMedia.html.abstract: Describes the input media file in a transcription request.

Classes/AWSTranscribeMedicalTranscript.h.name: AWSTranscribeMedicalTranscript
Classes/AWSTranscribeMedicalTranscript.h.abstract: Identifies the location of a medical transcript.

Classes/AWSTranscribeMedicalTranscriptio.name: AWSTranscribeMedicalTranscriptionJob
Classes/AWSTranscribeMedicalTranscriptio.abstract: The data structure that contains the information for a medical transcription job.

Classes/AWSTranscribeMedicalTranscriptio.name: AWSTranscribeMedicalTranscriptionJobSummary
Classes/AWSTranscribeMedicalTranscriptio.abstract: Provides summary information about a transcription job.

Classes/AWSTranscribeMedicalTranscriptio.name: AWSTranscribeMedicalTranscriptionSetting
Classes/AWSTranscribeMedicalTranscriptio.abstract: Optional settings for the StartMedicalTranscriptionJob operation.

Classes/AWSTranscribeModelSettings.html.name: AWSTranscribeModelSettings
Classes/AWSTranscribeModelSettings.html.abstract: The object used to call your custom language model to your transcription job.

Classes/AWSTranscribeNonTalkTimeFilter.h.name: AWSTranscribeNonTalkTimeFilter
Classes/AWSTranscribeNonTalkTimeFilter.h.abstract: An object that enables you to configure your category to be applied to call analytics jobs where either the customer or agent was interrupted.

Classes/AWSTranscribeRelativeTimeRange.h.name: AWSTranscribeRelativeTimeRange
Classes/AWSTranscribeRelativeTimeRange.h.abstract: An object that allows percentages to specify the proportion of the call where you would like to apply a filter. For example, you can specify the first half of the call. You can also specify the period of time between halfway through to three-quarters of the way through the call. Because the length of conversation can vary between calls, you can apply relative time ranges across all calls.

Classes/AWSTranscribeRule.html.name: AWSTranscribeRule
Classes/AWSTranscribeRule.html.abstract: A condition in the call between the customer and the agent that you want to filter for.

Classes/AWSTranscribeSentimentFilter.htm.name: AWSTranscribeSentimentFilter
Classes/AWSTranscribeSentimentFilter.htm.abstract: An object that enables you to specify a particular customer or agent sentiment. If at least 50 percent of the conversation turns (the back-and-forth between two speakers) in a specified time period match the specified sentiment, Amazon Transcribe will consider the sentiment a match.

Classes/AWSTranscribeSubtitles.html.name: AWSTranscribeSubtitles
Classes/AWSTranscribeSubtitles.html.abstract: Generate subtitles for your batch transcription job.

Classes/AWSTranscribeSubtitlesOutput.htm.name: AWSTranscribeSubtitlesOutput
Classes/AWSTranscribeSubtitlesOutput.htm.abstract: Specify the output format for your subtitle file.

Classes/AWSTranscribeTag.html.name: AWSTranscribeTag
Classes/AWSTranscribeTag.html.abstract: A key:value pair that adds metadata to a resource used by Amazon Transcribe. For example, a tag with the key:value pair ‘Department’:’Sales’ might be added to a resource to indicate its use by your organization’s sales department.

Classes/AWSTranscribeTranscriptFilter.ht.name: AWSTranscribeTranscriptFilter
Classes/AWSTranscribeTranscriptFilter.ht.abstract: Matches the output of the transcription to either the specific phrases that you specify, or the intent of the phrases that you specify.

Classes/AWSTranscribeTranscriptionJob.ht.abstract: Describes an asynchronous transcription job that was created with the StartTranscriptionJob operation.

Classes/AWSTranscribeTranscriptionJobSum.abstract: Provides a summary of information about a transcription job.
